@startuml
title Player Controller System

left to right direction
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

package "Input Layer" {
  class PlayerController {
    - movement : Movement
    - facing : Facing2D
    - aimPivot : AimPivot2D
    - mainCamera : Camera
    + OnMove(context : InputAction.CallbackContext) : void
    - Awake() : void
    - Update() : void
  }
}

package "Movement Layer" {
  class Movement {
    - moveSpeed : float = 5f
    - rb2d : Rigidbody2D
    - moveInput : Vector2
    + SetmoveInput(input : Vector2) : void
    - Start() : void
    - FixedUpdate() : void
  }
}

package "Facing Layer" {
  together {
    class Facing2D {
      - faceRight : bool = true
      + IsFacingRight : bool { get }
      + SetDirection(direction : float) : void
      - Flip() : void
    }

    class AimPivot2D {
      - aimPivot : Transform
      + SetDirection(direction : Vector2) : void
      + ResetRotation() : void
    }
  }
}

package "Unity Objects" {
  class Camera
  class Rigidbody2D
  class Transform
}

PlayerController --> Movement : move input
PlayerController --> Facing2D : facing
PlayerController --> AimPivot2D : aim
PlayerController --> Camera : mouse position

Movement --> Rigidbody2D : MovePosition()
AimPivot2D --> Transform : rotate pivot

PlayerController -[hidden]right- Movement
Movement -[hidden]right- Facing2D
Facing2D -[hidden]down- AimPivot2D
Movement -[hidden]down- Camera
AimPivot2D -[hidden]right- Transform
Movement -[hidden]right- Rigidbody2D

note right of PlayerController
Main flow:
1. Read move input from Input System
2. Send input to Movement
3. Read mouse position from camera
4. Compute look direction
5. Update Facing2D and AimPivot2D
end note

note bottom of Rigidbody2D
Moves player in FixedUpdate
using Rigidbody2D.MovePosition.
end note

note bottom of Transform
Rotates weapon/aim pivot
to face mouse direction.
end note

@enduml
